:: title ::

# Even Backstage Agrees

:: content ::

Backstage v1.40 shipped `@backstage/plugin-mcp-actions-backend`

```ts {all|4-5|7-9|all} twoslash
// @noErrors
// Backstage v1.40 - your portal becomes an MCP server

import { createBackendModule } from '@backstage/backend-plugin-api';
import { mcpActionsPlugin } from '@backstage/plugin-mcp-actions-backend';

// Every scaffolder action becomes an MCP tool
// Every catalog entity becomes queryable via conversation
// Your portal becomes an MCP server

const backend = createBackend();
backend.add(mcpActionsPlugin);
```

<Admonition title="Your portal isn't dead" color="emerald-light">
It's becoming your **MCP server**. The catalog is still the source of truth. MCP is how agents and conversations access it.
</Admonition>

<!--
This is the validation. Backstage itself shipped MCP support. Every scaffolder action becomes a tool. Every catalog entity becomes queryable from the conversation. Backstage isn't dying - it's evolving from a destination to infrastructure.
-->

